The presentation of abdominal pain starting after eating and persisting for 6 hours, accompanied by vomiting and tenderness in the right upper quadrant, suggests gallstone disease. The inability to visualize any gallstones on ultrasound may be due to the patient's body habitus. Acalculous cholecystitis would not have gallstones present, while cancer of the biliary tree and pancreatic inflammation would have abnormal liver function tests, amylase, and lipase levels.
